1
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:03,200
<i>If Uncle Ree can eat it, so can I.</i>

2
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:09,560
Good heavens. How scandalous.

3
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,240
The Kam Cheng jar…

4
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:15,200
<i>The lowest point of my life</i>

5
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,160
<i>all started with that man named Kajorn.</i>

6
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:20,200
Even if Rajit kicks me out, I'm not going.

7
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,960
You pathetic pimp.

8
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,960
I don't care about
the situation with Suda,

9
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:28,560
but if you lay a finger on Rajit,

10
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:29,760
you're a dead man.

11
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:33,760
Help me.

12
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:41,480
Have you found out yet

13
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:43,800
who's selling the contraband ahead of us?

14
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:46,000
I don't know yet,

15
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:48,280
but they must have some connections.

16
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,760
They wouldn't be able
to pull this off alone.

17
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,720
Let's drop that for now.

18
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:58,080
I have a much higher priority for you.

19
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:02,880
Name it. Going this long without a raid,

20
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:05,120
my hands are going to start itching.

21
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:13,240
Eliminate Thatri.

22
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:19,560
Not only is he stealing my inheritance,

23
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:21,080
he's also plotting with the Japanese

24
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:23,040
and the District Chief against us.

25
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:27,560
And just today, he threw away
a fortune just to play hero.

26
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:29,160
If we let him live,

27
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:31,480
he'll end up being the death of me.

28
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:33,720
Leave it to me. I'll take care of it.

29
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:36,160
The only reason
I had to come crawling to you

30
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:39,120
is because of him.
I'm going to make him pay for this.

31
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:30,560
BARBER SHOP

32
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,520
A haircut and a shave, please.

33
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,400
Right away, sir. Please, come inside.

34
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:41,240
BARBER SHOP

35
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:58,560
What happened to the other barber?

36
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:00,200
He suddenly had a stomachache.

37
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:02,200
I'll be taking care of you instead.

38
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,360
Eliminate Thatri.

39
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:23,760
How would you like it done?

40
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:27,440
Give me a shave as well.
It's getting a bit long.

41
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:28,480
Right away, sir.

42
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:02,920
Excuse me, sir.

43
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,000
Mr. Thatri.

44
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:47,880
District Chief.

45
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,280
Sorry for making you meet me here.

46
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:56,880
I needed a shave and a haircut.

47
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:57,960
This would save us time.

48
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,200
It's okay.

49
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:03,000
Any word on Black Beard?

50
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:08,560
Nothing yet. He's gone
completely underground.

51
00:07:08,640 --> 00:07:11,520
Colonel Nakamura is preoccupied
with the war,

52
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,440
so I haven't pressed him for updates.

53
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:17,480
That bandit is slick.

54
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:22,240
Bold enough when robbing innocents.
Now, he hides like a turtle in its shell.

55
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:25,000
What a total coward.

56
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:29,520
Like I said,

57
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:32,600
Black Beard must have someone backing him.

58
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,520
Someone powerful.

59
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:37,520
Otherwise, he wouldn't
be able to stay this quiet.

60
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:41,320
Scum clings to scum.

61
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,000
But honestly,

62
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:47,120
whoever hires a brainless thug
like Black Beard

63
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,400
can't be that smart either.

64
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:54,120
He's just brutal, greedy, and stupid.

65
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:57,320
That's why his boss leads him around
by the nose so easily.

66
00:07:57,400 --> 00:08:00,840
It just shows the mastermind
has poor judgment,

67
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:04,280
using an idiot as their puppet.

68
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:07,880
If I ever catch him,
I'll kick his ass straight into jail.

69
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,440
Count me in.

70
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:22,200
How does that idiot always get so lucky?

71
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,600
Boss, can you get me

72
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:26,480
into the Som Song Saeng house?

73
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,120
I won't screw it up this time.

74
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:32,000
Too risky. If they investigate,

75
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,760
the trail will lead straight back to me.

76
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,919
Then how are we supposed
to get close to him?

77
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,600
I have an idea.

78
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:59,600
The Vegetarian Festival is a tradition
among the Chinese here in Phuket,

79
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:01,160
though its reach remains limited.

80
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:05,560
I truly wish more people would adopt it
for their own spiritual merit.

81
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:07,160
What do you think about it, Thatri?

82
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,120
Making merit is secondary to me,

83
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:12,520
but I'm all for it.
Food is strictly rationed right now.

84
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,840
If half the province gave up meat
and switched to vegetables,

85
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:18,120
it would stretch our resources.

86
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,640
If there's anything we can do to help,

87
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:24,080
please just let us know.

88
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:27,120
I do need your help.

89
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:30,840
I want you two to coordinate
with the local shrines

90
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,080
and government offices.

91
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:34,520
I'll handle the downtown shrines myself.

92
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:36,480
Rajit, you take the one near the mines,

93
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:40,360
and Thatri, could you please handle
the government offices?

94
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,000
Of course.

95
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:45,840
I'll head out first thing tomorrow.

96
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:47,960
Thank you, dear.

97
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:51,000
And here are the details

98
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:54,560
of who to contact and what to do.
I've written everything down for you.

99
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,880
I'm counting on you, Thatri.

100
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:58,880
You got it, Fuang.

101
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:03,400
Oh, it's late already.

102
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,320
Off to bed now, you two.

103
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,440
Alright.

104
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,520
Here it is, sir.

105
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,440
Thanks.

106
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,720
Sure you don't want to ride?

107
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:36,560
I'm fine, really.
The shrine is pretty close.

108
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:38,560
Nit and I can easily walk there,

109
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:39,880
no wheels needed.

110
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,240
You don't know how to ride, do you?

111
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:45,200
Go tease someone younger, Uncle Ree.

112
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:47,320
I'm not a kid anymore.

113
00:10:57,640 --> 00:10:58,640
Let's go.

114
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:07,880
District Chief.

115
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:08,880
Miss Rajit.

116
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,240
Why are you on foot?

117
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,480
Where is your car?

118
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:14,880
With the ongoing war,

119
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:18,000
there's a fuel shortage,
so we're walking instead.

120
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:21,920
Is Mr. Thatri at the house?

121
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,200
I need to talk to him.

122
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,400
Uncle Ree isn't home.

123
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:28,400
He's going to the government offices
to coordinate the Vegetarian Festival.

124
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:30,160
We just parted ways.

125
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:32,160
If you hurry, you can still catch him.

126
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:34,080
Come on. I'll show you the way.

127
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,720
- Thank you.
- Let's go, Nid.

128
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,040
You…

129
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,080
Recognize me now?

130
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:57,720
I was ready to slit your throat yesterday.

131
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,400
But doing it today works just fine.

132
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:02,520
You're Zhang Gong Cheng.

133
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,840
You think you're so good, Thatri?

134
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,600
Want to see how a bullet tastes?

135
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,120
Uncle Ree!

136
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,120
Hand the girl over,

137
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,960
or Thatri gets a bullet.

138
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:13,440
Hurry up!

139
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:28,360
Miss Rajit!

140
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:32,320
Rajit.

141
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:52,200
Nid, stay right here,
it's too dangerous to follow.

142
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:53,800
Move!

143
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:02,520
Don't you dare touch her.

144
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:05,920
Don't worry, District Chief.

145
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,560
They won't dare harm me.

146
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:10,040
It's fine. I'll protect her.

147
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:11,480
Shut your mouth.

148
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:15,120
If you follow us, they're both dead.

149
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:19,480
Get on the boat.

150
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,080
Now.

151
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,360
Primprao. Nareewan.

152
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:45,360
Did you come to help Rajit
prep the vegetarian dishes?

153
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,280
That's right.

154
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:49,080
We agreed to make them together

155
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:51,120
and bring some back for our families.

156
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:53,840
What a waste.

157
00:14:58,360 --> 00:14:59,360
District Chief?

158
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:02,680
District Chief, what's wrong?

159
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,400
Mr. Thatri and Miss Rajit

160
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:07,320
have been kidnapped by Zhang Gong Cheng.

161
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:08,720
Huh?

162
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,400
Rajit…

163
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:23,640
Someone really is out to get Rajit.

164
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:25,080
I knew it.

165
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:28,520
God knows what's happening
to them right now.

166
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,760
We've already alerted the authorities.
I'm sure they'll be fine.

167
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,280
Right, District Chief?

168
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,680
Yes. The moment
the police are ready to move,

169
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:40,880
I will lead the search party myself.

170
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:45,680
Oh my God.

171
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:48,000
I wonder how Rajit and Thatri

172
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,160
are holding up.

173
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:52,400
I'm so worried.

174
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:54,320
What if something happened to them?

175
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:56,800
What a fake b--

176
00:15:58,280 --> 00:15:59,760
I'm calling it like it is.

177
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:03,040
I get it, but read the room.

178
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,440
I'm so stressed.

179
00:16:08,520 --> 00:16:12,160
It's killing me. I'm going to get
my hair done to calm my nerves.

180
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:16,600
Bye now.

181
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:27,320
The men are assembled
and ready to move, sir.

182
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,040
District Chief.

183
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,120
Let me come with you.

184
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:34,160
I want to help bring Rajit back.

185
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,760
How are you holding up?

186
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:42,600
Are you seasick?

187
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:45,880
I'm fine. What about you, Uncle Ree?

188
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:47,520
I'm okay.

189
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,080
Get all your sweet talk out now.

190
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:51,240
You'll both be dead anyway.

191
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,480
What do you want?

192
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:54,320
I want you dead.

193
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:55,680
Why?

194
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:57,080
What do you gain from killing me?

195
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,200
Because you've been teaming up
with the Japanese

196
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:01,360
and the police to hunt me down.

197
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,760
Don't play dumb with me.

198
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:10,400
Hey.

199
00:17:11,040 --> 00:17:12,680
You're going after Rajit?

200
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:15,079
I heard the news from the servants.
I'm coming with you.

201
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,720
Word travels fast, huh?

202
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,480
Why exactly are you going?

203
00:17:20,079 --> 00:17:22,319
You'll only be a liability to the police.

204
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:25,000
I think you're the liability here.

205
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:26,720
A pampered man like you

206
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,480
wouldn't last a second against a bandit.

207
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:30,360
- Want to test it with a fist?
- Bring it on.

208
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:31,720
Enough, both of you!

209
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:37,320
You're both staying right here.

210
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,480
You'll just be a distraction for my men.

211
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:00,520
How far can this tiny boat

212
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,720
actually take you, Black Beard?

213
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:05,760
Oh, right, you lost the beard.

214
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:09,440
Should I call you Baby Face instead?

215
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:10,840
You talk too much.

216
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:14,200
Hey! Speed this thing up.

217
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:15,560
Yes, Boss.

218
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:17,920
Speed it up.

219
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:20,840
There's no escape. Surrender now.

220
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:23,920
The District Chief is probably
mobilized the entire force after us.

221
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,360
Only an idiot would surrender.

222
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:28,520
This tiny boat won't go far.

223
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:29,920
You're going to run out of fuel.

224
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:35,360
Do you really think
I'm crossing the sea in this boat?

225
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:36,280
Look over there.

226
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,640
That's my real ride.

227
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:02,600
Move.

228
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:06,480
Are you safe, Boss?

229
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:07,840
Safe and sound.

230
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:10,840
Is everything ready?

231
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:11,760
All set, Boss.

232
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:27,080
What the hell?

233
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,880
Let's go, Rajit. Jump!

234
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:53,600
Get down there and drag them back!

235
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:54,880
After all those shots,

236
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,640
they're definitely dead, Boss.

237
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:58,040
Dead bodies bleed, you idiot.

238
00:19:58,120 --> 00:19:59,240
I said get down there.

239
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:00,320
Hurry up!

240
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,480
Boss,

241
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:04,680
there's a boat coming this way.
Might be a police boat.

242
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:07,120
Give me the binoculars.

243
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:10,480
- What the hell?
- Here, Boss.

244
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:21,920
Ugh! It's the police!

245
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,560
What are your orders, Boss?

246
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:26,240
We retreat, you idiot. Move!

247
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:27,160
- Move!
- Let's go!

248
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:35,920
District Chief.

249
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,520
Boat spotted.

250
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:41,160
Right over there, sir.

251
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:48,080
That's Zhang Gong Cheng.

252
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:49,840
- Punch the engine!
- Yes, sir.

253
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:52,840
More speed!

254
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:36,040
The cops definitely know
where we are, Boss.

255
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,720
Light it up. Release the toxic smoke!

256
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:44,640
- Yes.
- Hurry up!

257
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:46,480
Light the fire!

258
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:47,720
Now!

259
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,120
Hurry up!

260
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:56,080
Feed the flames!

261
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:57,320
Hurry up! Come on.

262
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:59,640
Faster.

263
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:05,760
Keep it coming.

264
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:08,240
- Come on.
- Hurry up!

265
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:09,400
Hurry up.

266
00:23:15,680 --> 00:23:17,720
What is this smoke? It's burning my eyes.

267
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:20,320
Those bastards must be burning
some toxic herbs.

268
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:21,600
What do we do, Chief?

269
00:23:21,680 --> 00:23:22,840
We're trapped downwind.

270
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:25,200
Turn the boat around.

271
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:27,240
Fall back, now!

272
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:28,800
- Retreat!
- Retreat!

273
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:37,640
They're retreating, Boss.

274
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:39,040
And so are we.

275
00:23:39,120 --> 00:23:41,120
- You want to wait until they come back?
- Got it.

276
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:43,640
Move it at full speed.

277
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:11,360
Uncle Ree.

278
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:14,320
Uncle Ree.

279
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:17,600
Uncle Ree. Wake up.

280
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:59,600
Uncle Ree.

281
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:03,120
Uncle Ree. Wake up.

282
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,640
Uncle Ree!

283
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:06,320
Uncle Ree.

284
00:25:09,640 --> 00:25:11,040
Uncle Ree.

285
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,600
Rajit. Are you okay?

286
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:31,960
Are you hurt?

287
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:34,320
You weren't shot, right?

288
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:37,760
I'm perfectly fine.

289
00:25:39,160 --> 00:25:43,080
Who gave you permission
to share your breath with me underwater?

290
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:46,480
I was terrified you wouldn't make it.

291
00:25:46,560 --> 00:25:48,120
You were running out of air.

292
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:51,520
Then why…

293
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:56,000
Why didn't…

294
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:59,040
Why didn't you wait
until we hit the shore?

295
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:03,480
Do you have any idea
how hard it was for me

296
00:26:03,560 --> 00:26:07,320
to drag you out of the water?
You are incredibly heavy.

297
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:12,360
If you have enough energy to nag me,
you're definitely fine.

298
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:20,280
Well, where on earth are we?

299
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:23,360
I have no clue.

300
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:35,440
We're stuck here tonight.

301
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,800
We'll figure out a way back tomorrow.

302
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:48,680
Hurry it up.

303
00:26:48,760 --> 00:26:50,160
Don't ruin my auspicious hour.

304
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:52,640
Place them down. Carefully.

305
00:26:57,080 --> 00:26:59,200
Here. That's right.

306
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:10,320
Dear gods and spirits of the heavens,

307
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:13,520
please let those two vanish forever.

308
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:16,760
May they never find their way back.
If they truly never return,

309
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:20,040
I promise to offer you a hundred eggs.

310
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:27,440
Sister, please stop this.

311
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:29,560
You're making us look terrible.

312
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:32,880
Hush. Stop jinxing my blessing.

313
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:34,440
I thought she was struggling.

314
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:37,200
She can afford a hundred eggs
for the spirits,

315
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:38,560
but not for the workers?

316
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:39,720
Exactly.

317
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:41,800
She even curses Uncle Ree and our friend.

318
00:27:44,840 --> 00:27:47,280
If those two actually vanish for good,

319
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:50,280
I couldn't care less what anyone

320
00:27:50,360 --> 00:27:51,400
thinks of us.

321
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:55,560
District Chief.

322
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,200
District Chief.

323
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:01,400
How did it go?
Did you find Rajit and Uncle Ree?

324
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:03,120
No.

325
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:07,160
See? I told you to let me help,

326
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:08,600
but you wouldn't listen.

327
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:12,160
You clearly didn't have enough manpower
to take on those bandits.

328
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:18,080
Is he worried about her
or just her inheritance?

329
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:22,600
Even the police couldn't push through.
If you had come along,

330
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,680
you'd be a dead weight
before they even left.

331
00:28:29,080 --> 00:28:30,960
So you found absolutely no trace of them?

332
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:33,840
During our pursuit,

333
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:35,880
we engaged in a shootout with the pirates.

334
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:41,040
They managed to escape
with Rajit and Thatri.

335
00:28:43,840 --> 00:28:47,080
Poor Rajit and Thatri…

336
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:49,160
I'm so worried.

337
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,400
Hey, you.

338
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:57,240
Have a hundred eggs ready for tomorrow.

339
00:28:57,320 --> 00:29:00,320
I'm waking up at five to boil them.

340
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:10,560
Oh, I just can't. I'm going to bed.

341
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:12,080
Excuse me, District Chief!

342
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:18,080
Make sure the incense burns completely.

343
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:19,440
Every single stick.

344
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:46,680
Have a seat.

345
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:49,480
Thank you.

346
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:13,360
Must be nice being a man.

347
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:16,120
You can strip off your shirt
wherever you like.

348
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:19,560
Well, too bad.
You chose to be born a girl.

349
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:24,280
As if anyone gets a choice.

350
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:38,360
I didn't think you would know
how to build a campfire like this.

351
00:31:42,080 --> 00:31:43,320
Warming up yet?

352
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:46,560
Yes.

353
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:38,400
Uncle Ree.

354
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,960
Uncle Ree.

355
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:04,680
What on earth are you doing?

356
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:06,000
Fishing.

357
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:07,280
Fishing?

358
00:33:07,880 --> 00:33:11,280
And where did you get a fishing rod?

359
00:33:12,360 --> 00:33:13,400
Made it myself.

360
00:33:15,320 --> 00:33:18,800
Used mulberry bark for the line,
and the hook is made from a thorn.

361
00:33:21,200 --> 00:33:23,960
You're surprisingly resourceful.

362
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:26,880
I never imagined
you'd have survival skills like this.

363
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:29,600
I used to spend
a lot of time in the woods.

364
00:33:34,360 --> 00:33:35,680
Got one.

365
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:41,840
Here.

366
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:48,240
Smash its head and scale it.

367
00:33:48,320 --> 00:33:50,200
We're having grilled fish for breakfast.

368
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:51,520
Huh?

369
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:53,520
You want me…

370
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:55,560
to whack it on the head?

371
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:59,800
Well, yeah. If you don't do it, who will?

372
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:01,400
I'm going to gather more firewood.

373
00:34:07,920 --> 00:34:09,560
Fine.

374
00:34:14,960 --> 00:34:16,679
Wait a minute, Uncle Ree.

375
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:18,040
Uncle Ree!

376
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:19,159
Hurry up.

377
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:22,840
Do I really have to do this to you?

378
00:34:40,080 --> 00:34:41,199
Here.

379
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:44,560
Uncle Ree, I gathered
a whole bunch of wild fruits.

380
00:34:44,639 --> 00:34:45,920
We won't starve to death.

381
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:49,239
Good.

382
00:34:50,280 --> 00:34:53,040
What about the fish I asked you to prep?

383
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:55,280
I let it go.

384
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:00,200
You did what?

385
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:03,440
You let it go?

386
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:07,440
Sure did. I let it swim away.

387
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:16,600
What's with that face?

388
00:35:16,680 --> 00:35:20,000
I gathered all these fruits for us.

389
00:35:20,600 --> 00:35:22,560
We have plenty to eat, Uncle Ree.

390
00:35:22,640 --> 00:35:24,440
Plenty to eat…

391
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:29,360
ADISUAN PEARLS

392
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:37,560
Is everything taken care of?

393
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:39,400
They got away.

394
00:35:41,040 --> 00:35:42,200
Got away?

395
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:45,640
But the police reported
that you kidnapped them.

396
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:48,560
They haven't made it back yet?

397
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:56,200
They're hiding out somewhere then.

398
00:35:58,040 --> 00:35:59,920
Use this chance to hunt them down

399
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:01,320
and finish them off.

400
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:05,280
There's only one place

401
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:07,720
they could've drifted to.

402
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:10,120
Where?

403
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:11,720
The deserted island.

404
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:25,400
This is delicious.

405
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:33,440
I'm starving.

406
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:36,520
Thanks to someone,

407
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:38,400
I'm stuck eating bananas and coconuts

408
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:39,920
instead of a grilled fish.

409
00:36:40,520 --> 00:36:42,080
But it looked so pitiful.

410
00:36:42,160 --> 00:36:44,280
Right when I was about to whack it,

411
00:36:44,880 --> 00:36:47,960
it looked right at me.
That broke my heart.

412
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:51,960
Besides, your hook
already ripped its little mouth.

413
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:55,760
You've been eating fish your whole life.
Why pity them now?

414
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:58,200
That was different.

415
00:36:58,280 --> 00:37:01,240
We can easily survive on fruits for now.

416
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:03,520
If you're still hungry,

417
00:37:03,600 --> 00:37:05,320
I can go gather another one for you.

418
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:06,440
Nope.

419
00:37:07,560 --> 00:37:08,920
Forget it.

420
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:11,120
I'll go catch another fish myself.

421
00:37:11,200 --> 00:37:14,680
As for you, once it's grilled,
don't you even think about taking a bite.

422
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:19,400
I wouldn't eat it even if you paid me.

423
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:27,680
Freshly grilled fish,

424
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:29,400
hot and juicy.

425
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:31,360
I'll make sure to eat every last bite.

426
00:37:33,240 --> 00:37:34,680
Go right ahead.

427
00:37:36,640 --> 00:37:39,160
I think I'll just take
a midday nap instead.

428
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:40,680
I'm suddenly exhausted.

429
00:37:40,760 --> 00:37:42,200
Sleep all you want.

430
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:44,600
But don't expect me
to let you cuddle like last night.

431
00:37:50,240 --> 00:37:51,840
Stuck on a deserted island like this,

432
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:53,920
are you sure you can sleep?

433
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:11,560
I thought you'd have trouble sleeping.

434
00:38:12,360 --> 00:38:13,440
You're even snoring.

435
00:38:44,040 --> 00:38:45,120
Wait…

436
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:47,120
Did I really

437
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:50,280
cuddle with you last night?

438
00:38:58,200 --> 00:38:59,200
I'd better go fishing.

439
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:32,960
<i>Sleep all you want.</i>

440
00:39:33,040 --> 00:39:35,440
<i>But don't expect me</i>
<i>to let you cuddle like last night.</i>

441
00:39:50,080 --> 00:39:52,280
What on earth are you thinking, Rajit?

442
00:39:55,880 --> 00:39:57,280
Stop daydreaming.

443
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:06,760
<i>Snap out of it, Thatri.</i>

444
00:40:06,840 --> 00:40:08,320
<i>You're just an impostor here.</i>

445
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:11,880
<i>You're not a rich man with status anymore.</i>

446
00:40:12,680 --> 00:40:14,440
<i>You're completely broke.</i>

447
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:16,400
<i>How could you ever take care of Rajit?</i>

448
00:40:58,360 --> 00:40:59,600
Look, a boat.

449
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:03,320
Help! Help us!

450
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:04,920
There are people over here!

451
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:07,680
Help! Help!

452
00:41:23,680 --> 00:41:24,800
We're screwed.

453
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:28,520
Uncle Ree.

454
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:30,760
- Uncle Ree.
- Hmm?

455
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:33,000
Look over there.

456
00:41:38,360 --> 00:41:39,280
A boat.

457
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:43,240
Help! Help us!

458
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:46,520
Help! Help us!

459
00:41:49,720 --> 00:41:52,000
- Uncle Ree!
- Help--

460
00:41:52,080 --> 00:41:54,280
That's the pirate who kidnapped us.

461
00:42:00,520 --> 00:42:01,720
- Run.
- Huh?

462
00:42:19,400 --> 00:42:20,240
Are you okay?

463
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:23,160
I'm fine.

464
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:33,040
Let's go.

465
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:35,160
Ouch!

466
00:42:35,760 --> 00:42:37,080
After them.

467
00:42:45,760 --> 00:42:46,600
Are you okay?

468
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:50,600
I have to be okay.

469
00:42:56,680 --> 00:42:58,040
This way.

470
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:10,760
Huh?

471
00:43:11,480 --> 00:43:12,600
Where did they go?

472
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:17,480
Spread out and find them!

473
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:18,400
Yes, Boss.

474
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:30,680
We can't keep running like this.

475
00:43:33,720 --> 00:43:35,680
Then what are we going to do?

476
00:43:45,360 --> 00:43:46,400
See that guy over there?

477
00:43:49,360 --> 00:43:51,360
- Yes.
- Throw this rock

478
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:54,480
over that way to distract him.
I'll take him out from behind.

479
00:44:39,280 --> 00:44:41,840
- Are you sure you're okay?
- I am.

480
00:44:47,760 --> 00:44:49,200
Over there.

481
00:44:57,520 --> 00:44:58,720
After them!

482
00:45:32,280 --> 00:45:33,320
Hey, stop!

483
00:45:49,400 --> 00:45:50,280
You…

484
00:46:34,360 --> 00:46:35,440
I see the pirate boat.

485
00:46:35,520 --> 00:46:38,280
Thatri and Rajit must be on that island.

486
00:46:38,360 --> 00:46:40,080
- Head straight for it!
- Yes, sir.

487
00:46:40,160 --> 00:46:41,680
Full speed ahead. Now!

488
00:47:00,680 --> 00:47:03,640
Uncle Ree, what do we do?

489
00:47:11,400 --> 00:47:13,800
Uncle Ree, I have an idea.

490
00:47:14,560 --> 00:47:17,040
But it's a bit crazy.

491
00:47:18,160 --> 00:47:19,400
What is it?

492
00:47:45,760 --> 00:47:48,120
He's still breathing. Cuff him.

493
00:47:48,200 --> 00:47:49,240
Yes, sir.

494
00:47:56,920 --> 00:47:59,640
They couldn't have gone far. Let's move.

495
00:48:00,360 --> 00:48:01,200
Move.

496
00:48:09,280 --> 00:48:10,880
Hey there, pretty boy.

497
00:48:11,960 --> 00:48:13,720
You honestly think a piece of wood

498
00:48:15,080 --> 00:48:16,520
can stand against my blade?

499
00:48:22,760 --> 00:48:23,720
I don't know.

500
00:48:27,680 --> 00:48:29,400
Your time is up.

501
00:48:31,720 --> 00:48:33,080
Uncle Ree. Catch!

502
00:48:51,560 --> 00:48:52,920
One wrong move and she dies!

503
00:48:54,200 --> 00:48:55,480
Don't touch her.

504
00:48:55,560 --> 00:48:57,840
Take my life if you want,

505
00:48:57,920 --> 00:49:00,440
but don't touch her. Let her go.

506
00:49:14,240 --> 00:49:16,120
Your wish is my command, Thatri.

507
00:49:19,240 --> 00:49:21,480
Freeze!

508
00:49:25,720 --> 00:49:28,480
Drop the weapon, or I will shoot.

509
00:50:03,560 --> 00:50:04,400
Mr. Thatri.

510
00:50:06,800 --> 00:50:08,280
Took you long enough, District Chief.

511
00:50:10,200 --> 00:50:11,400
Uncle Ree…

512
00:50:13,360 --> 00:50:14,680
Rajit…

513
00:51:06,400 --> 00:51:07,240
From morning

514
00:51:07,320 --> 00:51:09,440
till evening,

515
00:51:10,160 --> 00:51:11,880
and I'm still not done peeling.

516
00:51:12,960 --> 00:51:15,040
Dear gods and spirits of the heavens,

517
00:51:15,120 --> 00:51:18,320
please be patient.
I promise I'll finish this.

518
00:51:19,840 --> 00:51:21,240
Don't do this, Pae.

519
00:51:21,320 --> 00:51:24,720
What if those two really never come back?

520
00:51:26,080 --> 00:51:27,200
Then that's even better.

521
00:51:27,280 --> 00:51:31,000
If they're gone,
I'll double it to 200 eggs.

522
00:51:32,760 --> 00:51:33,960
Hurry up and help me.

523
00:51:38,800 --> 00:51:39,600
Miss Rajit.

524
00:51:40,200 --> 00:51:41,560
- Rajit.
- Rajit.

525
00:51:49,920 --> 00:51:52,560
The righteous always survive, you know.

526
00:51:52,640 --> 00:51:56,120
As for the wicked,
heaven never takes their side.

527
00:51:57,560 --> 00:51:58,720
Thatri.

528
00:51:58,800 --> 00:52:00,360
Thatri, in the flesh.

529
00:52:00,440 --> 00:52:02,440
The guy you so desperately
wanted dead is here.

530
00:52:05,760 --> 00:52:06,800
That's it.

531
00:52:06,880 --> 00:52:07,840
I'm done.

532
00:52:07,920 --> 00:52:09,440
Cancel the offering.

533
00:52:09,520 --> 00:52:12,160
The deities around here are useless.
My wish didn't come true.

534
00:52:15,480 --> 00:52:17,080
Sister Pae…

535
00:52:25,200 --> 00:52:26,720
Rajit, are you alright?

536
00:52:27,440 --> 00:52:28,600
Miss Rajit.

537
00:52:29,880 --> 00:52:31,080
Are you alright?

538
00:52:32,600 --> 00:52:34,640
Your fan club is still going strong.

539
00:52:40,040 --> 00:52:41,360
Thank you for bringing us back.

540
00:52:41,960 --> 00:52:44,120
I'll take my leave then.

541
00:52:44,760 --> 00:52:46,080
See you around.

542
00:52:51,600 --> 00:52:54,040
Let's go, Rajit. You need some rest.

543
00:52:56,160 --> 00:52:57,080
Easy now.

544
00:53:30,040 --> 00:53:31,360
Let me see your leg.

545
00:53:53,080 --> 00:53:54,080
It's a bit cold.

546
00:54:31,880 --> 00:54:33,280
Thank you.

547
00:54:37,000 --> 00:54:38,160
So, how are you holding up?

548
00:54:41,280 --> 00:54:42,960
Which part do you want to hear first?

549
00:54:43,560 --> 00:54:44,880
If it's about my headache,

550
00:54:45,480 --> 00:54:48,720
Kajorn and Vijarn are giving me
a massive headache as usual.

551
00:54:48,800 --> 00:54:51,840
But if it's about my ankle,
as you can see,

552
00:54:52,840 --> 00:54:56,520
it's still bruised,
but it doesn't really hurt anymore.

553
00:54:59,720 --> 00:55:02,760
And what about your comfort?

554
00:55:03,840 --> 00:55:05,440
My comfort?

555
00:55:12,680 --> 00:55:15,520
You know, being comforted

556
00:55:15,600 --> 00:55:17,640
by the fact that even if
you end up on an island

557
00:55:19,040 --> 00:55:21,160
or trapped in this chaotic house,

558
00:55:23,040 --> 00:55:25,200
you still have me right by your side.

559
00:56:02,040 --> 00:56:03,560
- I came to ask--
- Would you

560
00:56:03,640 --> 00:56:05,600
come to the Lantern Festival
tonight with me?

561
00:56:10,760 --> 00:56:13,480
Mr. Thatri, someone's here to see you.

562
00:56:16,280 --> 00:56:19,240
- An old flame showing up here?
- Exactly.

563
00:56:19,320 --> 00:56:22,880
<i>Her husband literally came with her,</i>
<i>and you're still trying to have an affair?</i>

564
00:56:22,960 --> 00:56:24,480
If you're going to act like this,

565
00:56:24,560 --> 00:56:27,240
let's just split the inheritance
once and for all.

566
00:56:27,320 --> 00:56:29,200
Fine. Let's split it up and cut ties.

567
00:56:29,280 --> 00:56:32,880
Are you really moving to Bangkok
while the inheritance is being settled?

568
00:56:32,960 --> 00:56:35,160
I'm going to rebuild my life over there.

569
00:57:05,440 --> 00:57:07,440
Subtitle translation by:
Khathathong Thongtumlueng
